file = "meteor_test_2000.csv"

meteor_kv = []

with open(file, mode='r') as input_file:
    rows = []
    for row in input_file:
        rows.append(row.rstrip('\n').split(","))
    keys = rows[0]
    for values in rows[1:]:
        meteor_kv.append(dict(zip(keys, values)))
print(meteor_kv)
